1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,586
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,670 --> 00:00:07,382
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,717 --> 00:00:10,677
- ♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,971
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,018
What is that for?

7
00:00:18,101 --> 00:00:20,145
[Atoy] <i>So I can talk to Sister Norma.</i>

8
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:23,148
<i>They said she's the only one who knows</i>
<i>where Ibyang really came from.</i>

9
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:26,568
[Audrey] <i>I hope you can still give me</i>
<i>a chance to be with her.</i>

10
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:29,654
[Ibyang] Don't sit there, miss.
Um, the paint isn't dry yet.

11
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:31,698
[Red] <i>We can't persuade those nuns.</i>

12
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,491
<i>They need to be threatened. Tonight.</i>

13
00:00:33,575 --> 00:00:35,618
Let's corner Sister Norma.

14
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:39,205
[Atoy] <i>Sister Norma, I just…</i>
<i>need to know something from you.</i>

15
00:00:39,789 --> 00:00:41,499
<i>Something important… Sister?</i>

16
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:42,834
[Atoy] Wait, wait.

17
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:44,753
[Audrey] <i>Is your name Ibyang?</i>

18
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:46,671
Are you being bullied at your school?

19
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:48,882
I didn't do anything to them.

20
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:51,551
I'll just cut them from in my mind.

21
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:53,344
[Atoy] <i>Sister, do you remember her?</i>

22
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:55,430
<i>She's eight years old now.</i>

23
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:57,932
<i>Maybe there's a way you can tell me where</i>

24
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:00,852
<i>I can find her parents.</i>

25
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,228
[gunshot, glass breaks]

26
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:03,563
[music swells]

27
00:01:03,646 --> 00:01:06,191
- Where is Sister Norma? [grunts]
- I don't know, sir!

28
00:01:06,274 --> 00:01:07,567
PREVIOUSLY

29
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:19,621
[music fades]

30
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:25,585
[crickets chirping in distance]

31
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:35,929
I'll leave you now, Sister, okay?

32
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:37,096
All right.

33
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:38,014
[clicks]

34
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:41,768
[door clicks shut]

35
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:50,985
[suspicious music playing]

36
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:10,839
[music fades]

37
00:02:10,922 --> 00:02:13,007
Brother Temyo?

38
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,676
Come, eat!

39
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:17,720
[crickets chirping in the distance]

40
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:18,972
- [gasps]
- [tense music playing]

41
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:20,223
Brother Temyo!

42
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:21,683
My God, Lord!

43
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:23,935
Brother Temyo!

44
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:27,105
- [panicked breathing]
- [music concludes]

45
00:02:28,398 --> 00:02:32,902
We'll send a letter of request
to the archbishop's office, okay?

46
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:34,654
Yes, Sister.

47
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,865
[tense music playing]

48
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:37,991
[nun breathing panicky]

49
00:02:38,074 --> 00:02:40,034
Sister Ludy! [gasping]

50
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:43,413
Brother Temyo is lying outside! He's dead!

51
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:45,540
[Sister Ludy, in English] Mother of God!
Are-- Are you sure?

52
00:02:45,623 --> 00:02:47,500
Yes, I checked his pulse.

53
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:49,168
- He's gone!
- [indistinct]

54
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,504
Sister, I'll call an ambulance
and the police.

55
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:52,964
[Sister Ludy] All right.

56
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:54,549
- [Red] No, stay there.
- [gasps]

57
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,009
- [Red] Go back!
- [Mongki] Back!

58
00:02:56,092 --> 00:02:57,427
[Mongki] Oops, oops, step back.

59
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:58,636
- [ominous music playing]
- [nun mutters]

60
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,597
[nun sobbing]

61
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,516
[Red] Nothing will happen
unless you tell me where Sister Norma is.

62
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,351
Why would I do that?

63
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:06,895
Who are you?

64
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:09,731
Why are you all looking for Sister Norma?

65
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:12,066
[Red] Don't meddle, Sister.

66
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,359
Will you tell me or not?

67
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:15,778
- [Red] What?!
- [nuns squeal, gasp]

68
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:19,824
For the love of God. Enough!

69
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:22,493
I'll show you where Sister Norma is!

70
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,037
[tense music playing]

71
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,914
[Red] Come with me. Tie them up.

72
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:27,707
- [Mongki] Where?
- [Red] Come here.

73
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,292
- Come here.
- [nuns crying]

74
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:30,501
- [Mongki] Sister, come here.
- [Red] Come!

75
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:31,628
[Mongki] Sit!

76
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:35,465
[music swells]

77
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:37,091
- [music fades]
- [gasping]

78
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,343
- Sister May!
- Oh?

79
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:41,304
Armed men came in.

80
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:43,681
They pointed guns
at Sister Ludy. [gasping]

81
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:45,850
Why? What do they want?

82
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:47,727
[Sister May] We don't have money here!

83
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:50,396
They're looking for Sister Norma!

84
00:03:51,105 --> 00:03:52,440
Let's report to the police.

85
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,399
Go to the office. Come on!

86
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:55,777
- [tense music playing]
- [gasping]

87
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:05,453
- [Red] Where?
- [crying]

88
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:07,330
- The-- There at…
- Huh?

89
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:10,708
[tense action music playing]

90
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:14,087
St. Therese.

91
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,171
- Yes, she's there.
- [Red] Here?

92
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,089
[Sister Ludy] Yes.

93
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:22,011
‪[crying]

94
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:25,223
‪[gasping]

95
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:31,396
[suave theme music playing]

96
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:33,314
[motorcycle revving]

97
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:34,274
[sewing machine whirring]

98
00:04:34,357 --> 00:04:35,233
[scratches]

99
00:04:35,316 --> 00:04:37,235
[snipping]

100
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:41,114
[sewing machine whirring]

101
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:42,323
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots blasting]

102
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:44,492
[gunshots blasting]

103
00:04:44,575 --> 00:04:46,786
[clicking]

104
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:48,871
[snipping]

105
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,999
[music swells]

106
00:04:58,089 --> 00:05:02,427
[crickets chirping in distance]

107
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:18,818
[ominous music playing]

108
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:43,468
[music fades]

109
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:45,428
- [Sister Ludy whimpering]
- [Red] Hey!

110
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:46,596
[Red] Where?

111
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:47,680
[suspicious music playing]

112
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:49,348
[Sister Ludy] Sister Norma!

113
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:51,768
- Don't! Run now!
- [Red] Her?

114
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,561
[Sister Ludy] Run! Run! Leave her!

115
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:57,065
[grunting]

116
00:05:58,900 --> 00:05:59,734
[thumps]

117
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:01,611
[Red grunts]

118
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:14,290
[Red] Stop!

119
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:17,335
[gunshots blasting]

120
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:19,045
[tense music playing]

121
00:06:19,128 --> 00:06:20,421
[Atoy] Sister, you should escape now!

122
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:25,468
[grunts]

123
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,889
[nuns sobbing]

124
00:06:29,972 --> 00:06:31,432
[Mongki] Oh, put this in your mouth!

125
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:32,725
[sobbing]

126
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:35,311
What do you really want from Sister Norma?

127
00:06:35,394 --> 00:06:37,105
[nun 2] Let us go!

128
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:38,064
[Mongki] Enough!

129
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:40,483
- [sobbing]
- [Mongki] Just keep praying, Sister.

130
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,818
This will end soon.

131
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:43,653
[grunting]

132
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,404
- [gunshots blasting]
- [squealing, wailing]

133
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:48,199
[grunting]

134
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:50,118
[both whimpering]

135
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:51,953
We're begging you.

136
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:53,913
[sobs] Let us go!

137
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:56,374
We won't talk. Just don't hurt us.

138
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:57,416
- [Mongki] Shut up!
- [both whimpering]

139
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:00,211
You'll get hurt more
if you don't stop talking!

140
00:07:00,294 --> 00:07:01,963
Aren't you afraid of God?!

141
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:03,548
- [Mongki] I said enough!
- [wails]

142
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:05,174
- [grunts]
- [wails]

143
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,801
Please stop!

144
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,719
[wails]

145
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:12,432
- [Mongki grunts]
- [both whimpering]

146
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:24,110
[rousing music playing]

147
00:07:24,193 --> 00:07:27,238
[both whimpering]

148
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:37,039
[grunting and groaning]

149
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:39,375
[metal clinks]

150
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:42,962
[grunts]

151
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:46,424
[Atoy] If you want to get Sister Norma,
you'll have to go through me first.

152
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:48,342
- [Red, in English] So be it.
- [both grunt]

153
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:50,303
[grunts]

154
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:53,431
- [rock music playing]
- [panting]

155
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:10,740
- [grunting]
- [swishing, clanging]

156
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:13,951
- [grunting]
- [swishing, clanging]

157
00:08:14,035 --> 00:08:15,745
[grunting]

158
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:17,455
[tense music playing]

159
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:26,339
[grunts]

160
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,091
[grunts]

161
00:08:30,051 --> 00:08:32,428
[grunting and groaning]

162
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:39,143
[Red] Your voice sounds familiar to me.

163
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:40,937
Have I met you before?

164
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:43,689
Show your ugly face.

165
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:46,442
[Atoy] I bet you are way uglier than me.

166
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:50,238
[grunting]

167
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:00,915
[gunshots blasting]

168
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:02,667
[Mongki] Boss, what happened?!

169
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,670
Deal with him.

170
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:07,171
Sister Norma is mine.

171
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,048
[grunts]

172
00:09:11,884 --> 00:09:14,762
[pensive music playing]

173
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:20,393
- [tense music playing]
- [heavy breathing]

174
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,129
[Red grunts, sniffs]

175
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:56,971
[phone ringing]

176
00:09:57,054 --> 00:09:57,888
‪[sighs]

177
00:09:59,348 --> 00:10:01,267
Another distraction. [inhales]

178
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:03,269
- [phone blips]
- [sighs]

179
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,855
- Hello?
- Why are you taking so long?

180
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:06,814
[sighs]

181
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:08,149
Ah, we're still fixing it.

182
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:11,193
[sighs] You're having trouble
making a nun talk, Red?

183
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,989
We're working on it, right?

184
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:16,991
There was just a little mishap.

185
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:18,826
[in English] Eh,
what is that supposed to mean?

186
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:22,204
There's someone here
pretending to be a nun.

187
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,915
She was protected.

188
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,835
One. There's two of you there,
with Mongki, right?

189
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:30,296
What are you waiting for? Take her down!

190
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:31,881
We're fixing it, right?

191
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:33,924
What do you want?
Should we just chat here?

192
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:38,137
[in English] I just really, really hate it
when Dad is breathing down our necks!

193
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,723
Yes, I know. Especially for me.

194
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:43,434
Exactly. So, finish it already! Please!

195
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,896
[suspicious music playing]

196
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:48,731
- [phone blips]
- [sighs]

197
00:11:00,701 --> 00:11:03,704
- [dramatic sting]
- [tense music playing]

198
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,039
[Red] Got you.

199
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:24,392
[ominous music playing]

200
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,394
[Mongki] Whoever you are, come out now!

201
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:29,814
Surrender properly, you won't get hurt.

202
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:32,858
- [grunting and groaning]
- [bone cracks]

203
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:35,820
[grunting and groaning]

204
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:38,781
[heavy breathing]

205
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:39,865
[Atoy] Who are you?

206
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,076
What do you want from Sister Norma?

207
00:11:42,159 --> 00:11:43,411
[Mongki grunts] What are you?!

208
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:45,579
- [Mongki] A gay nun, huh?!
- [Atoy] You're sassing me, huh.

209
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,373
[growls]

210
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:50,292
[burbling]

211
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:52,461
- [panting]
- [Atoy] What? What's your answer?

212
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:54,004
Uh, nothing?

213
00:11:54,755 --> 00:11:56,674
[burbling]

214
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:57,925
[panting]

215
00:11:58,008 --> 00:11:59,051
[Atoy] Do you have an answer now?

216
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:02,012
[Mongki] You won't get anything from me!
[coughs, panting]

217
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,431
[Atoy] You should've said that earlier!

218
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,224
[grunts, groans]

219
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:08,269
[tense music playing]

220
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:21,407
[ominous music playing]

221
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:29,832
[metal clanks]

222
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,796
[Atoy] Sister Norma.

223
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:44,263
[tense music playing]

224
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:52,938
[nuns sobbing]

225
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:07,536
We need to help Sister Norma.

226
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,913
I know, Sister.

227
00:13:08,996 --> 00:13:11,040
I already called the police.
They're on their way.

228
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,418
[whimpering, gasping]

229
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,296
We need to split up.

230
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:18,422
All right.

231
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:34,104
[steps thudding]

232
00:13:36,315 --> 00:13:37,525
[Sister Norma gasping]

233
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:40,861
- [gunshot blasts]
- [squeals]

234
00:13:44,406 --> 00:13:45,574
- [intense music playing]
- [gasps]

235
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:47,326
[Red] You're such
a pain in the neck, Sister.

236
00:13:48,702 --> 00:13:50,704
Let's end this if you don't want
to get hurt.

237
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:55,334
[foreboding music playing]

238
00:13:59,004 --> 00:14:00,881
[Red, in English] Last chance, Sister.

239
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:06,554
Tell me where you took
the child Martina left with you.

240
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,932
Stop that nonsense vow of silence,

241
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,934
or I'll silence you
for the rest of your life.

242
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:15,896
I will not tell you
where she is, you devil!

243
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,690
You'll only hurt her!

244
00:14:18,315 --> 00:14:19,733
[dramatic sting]

245
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:21,026
[Red] Wow!

246
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,696
So, you can speak after all.

247
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:26,490
But I don't have time anymore.

248
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:28,784
I need your answer now.

249
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:31,203
[Red grunts] Ouch!

250
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:32,830
[grunting]

251
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:33,956
[tense music playing]

252
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:35,666
[gasps]

253
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:46,927
Sister Norma!

254
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:49,430
I know you! You're the one
causing trouble earlier!

255
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:53,100
You're the husband of Martina Regalia!

256
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,690
[crickets chirping in the distance]

257
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:01,233
[frustrated grunting]

258
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,319
[sighing]

259
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:08,949
- [mysterious music playing]
- [sighs]

260
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:09,867
‪[Martina sighs]

261
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:12,536
[Martina sighs, in English]
What are you looking at?

262
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:16,665
What scheme are you
and your husband up to again,

263
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,500
to drive you crazy like that?

264
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:22,171
We're looking for your child, Audrey.

265
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,256
[in English] A little gratitude, please?

266
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,928
You want a thank you?

267
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:32,723
But this is entirely your fault.

268
00:15:33,557 --> 00:15:37,519
And I know you're only doing this
to get a favor from Dad.

269
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:42,191
You really think highly
of yourself, don't you?

270
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,362
[in English] What?

271
00:15:47,446 --> 00:15:48,656
[in English] What are you gonna do?

272
00:15:55,287 --> 00:15:56,705
Too bad for you.

273
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:59,792
I need your answer now,
or you'll go straight to heaven.

274
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:02,836
- [ominous music playing]
- [gasps]

275
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:05,506
- [bell tolling]
- [groaning]

276
00:16:07,049 --> 00:16:08,258
[Atoy] Get down from there!

277
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,970
[grunts, groans]

278
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:11,887
‪[tense music playing]

279
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:22,064
[Mongki] This gay nun is such a menace.

280
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:25,192
[woman breathing heavily]

281
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:28,195
[nun 1] Did you see Sister Norma?

282
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:30,364
[nun 2] No. Is she in danger?

283
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:33,033
[nun 1] Yes,
someone is trying to kill her.

284
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,201
But don't worry.

285
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:35,911
The police are on their way.

286
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:37,496
[tense music playing]

287
00:16:37,579 --> 00:16:38,706
[Mongki] Police?

288
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:40,708
Boss and I need to escape now.

289
00:17:06,316 --> 00:17:07,735
[Red] Enough, Sister.

290
00:17:08,652 --> 00:17:10,279
Where's the child?

291
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:20,706
- Where's the child?!
- [squeals]

292
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:25,461
- [thuds]
- [Atoy gasps]

293
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:31,008
[epic music playing]

294
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,645
[nuns gasping]

295
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,563
Oh God.

296
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:50,027
Sister Norma.

297
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,987
[sobbing]

298
00:17:52,696 --> 00:17:54,531
[Atoy] Don't touch her.

299
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,745
[in English] Sister, I'm sorry.

300
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:05,084
Call an ambulance. Hurry!

301
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,796
- [sobbing]
- [somber music playing]

302
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,424
Fi-- Find her…

303
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:15,177
Find her.

304
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:19,264
[suspicious music playing]

305
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,429
[Ame] What a waste.
There's just a little left.

306
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:01,348
You didn't finish it, Karla.

307
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:02,683
Hey, there's just a little left.

308
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:04,143
[Tonet] Oh. [indistinct]

309
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:05,644
[Cita] Ibyang?

310
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,938
Are you waiting for someone?

311
00:19:08,021 --> 00:19:12,442
Ah, where is… Master Grumpy?

312
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:15,028
- Ah, ah…
- [Tonet] Yes, right?

313
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,573
Nothing, just busy.
Just looking for something.

314
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,116
Who, Miss Cita?

315
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:22,870
Ma, does he have a mission?

316
00:19:23,704 --> 00:19:25,622
Ah, no, this isn't work.

317
00:19:25,706 --> 00:19:27,583
He's handling something personal.

318
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:29,543
- [Karla, Tonet] Personal?
- Personal?

319
00:19:29,626 --> 00:19:32,004
- Really?
- But he doesn't even have a personal life.

320
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:34,715
- Personal, personal.
- Wha-- Whatever, whatever!

321
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:36,967
Ma, just say it.

322
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:39,636
Does he have a secret mission? About what?

323
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:48,395
[sneaky music playing]

324
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:55,986
ATOY IS LOOKING FOR SISTER NORMA
TO KNOW ABOUT IBYANG'S REAL PARENTS

325
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:58,071
I knew it!

326
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:01,200
- Atoy is looking for Ibyang's parents!
- [Karla] Ame!

327
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:01,992
[gasps]

328
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:03,535
- [in English] Sorry, sorry, sorry.
- Your mouth.

329
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:05,996
Master Grumpy is looking for my parents?

330
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:08,081
You're really something else.

331
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:09,249
Sorry.

332
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:14,880
[elated shrieking]

333
00:20:14,963 --> 00:20:18,050
I'm sure Master Grumpy will find them!

334
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,593
He's a badass!

335
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:21,470
[chuckles]

336
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:33,982
[gasping]

337
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:37,945
[pensive music playing]

338
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:40,197
[Red] Wait. I still
have to kill this menace!

339
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,323
[Mongki] Boss, the police are here!

340
00:20:42,407 --> 00:20:43,325
[Mongki] I know another way.
Come on! Let's go.

341
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:44,284
- [Mongki] Let's go!
- [Red grunts]

342
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:55,212
Who are you? [sobs]

343
00:20:55,295 --> 00:20:57,881
Why are you doing this to Sister Norma?!

344
00:20:57,965 --> 00:20:59,716
[Atoy] I didn't do this.

345
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:02,761
Why did you need to kill her?

346
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:03,971
[sobs]

347
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:06,014
[Atoy] I tried to protect her.

348
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,516
[sobs]

349
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,142
[Atoy] You take care of her now.

350
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:10,811
[sobs]

351
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:12,938
You're all the same.

352
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:15,691
You're the reason Sister Norma died!

353
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,151
[Atoy, in English] Sister, I'm sorry.

354
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,492
[sobbing]

355
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:31,290
[suspicious music playing]

356
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:50,600
[police siren wailing]

357
00:21:50,684 --> 00:21:51,768
[thuds]

358
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:09,703
[police siren wailing]

359
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:15,876
[sobbing]

360
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:23,175
[tense music playing]

361
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:33,435
[nun 1] He ran that way!

362
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,106
That way.

363
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:42,986
[leaves rustling]

364
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:44,321
Over there. Let's go!

365
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:48,158
[tense music playing]

366
00:23:13,183 --> 00:23:14,184
[Red] Let's go.

367
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:26,488
[police siren wailing]

368
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:39,626
[epic music playing]

369
00:23:39,709 --> 00:23:41,670
[Atoy] <i>I hope</i>
<i>you can forgive me, Sister Norma.</i>

370
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:43,547
<i>I failed to protect you.</i>

371
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:56,476
[electronic blipping]

372
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:06,486
Brother Atoy will never give up.

373
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,405
[Karla] <i>He will continue searching.</i>

374
00:24:08,488 --> 00:24:09,447
<i>You'll see.</i>

375
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:10,949
[sobs]

376
00:24:11,032 --> 00:24:14,035
Oh? Now that you've gathered
all the names of eight-year-old girls…

377
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:14,953
UP NEXT

378
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:17,205
…how will we find Audrey's real child?

379
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:18,123
[in English] It doesn't matter.

380
00:24:18,748 --> 00:24:20,834
We'll look for a child the same age
as Audrey's daughter.

381
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:22,335
[Martina, in English] <i>And then,</i>
<i>we'll convince</i>

382
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:24,129
<i>the parents to hand over their child.</i>

383
00:24:24,212 --> 00:24:26,089
- Ibyang!
- [magical twinkle]

384
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:27,090
[Audrey] Hi!

385
00:24:27,591 --> 00:24:29,009
[Atoy] Which one here has…

386
00:24:29,092 --> 00:24:30,760
yellow paint…

387
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:34,764
Maybe new paint, huh?

388
00:24:34,848 --> 00:24:37,893
[man] <i>Well, I painted</i>
<i>some benches over at the park.</i>

389
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,561
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

390
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:42,105
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

391
00:24:42,189 --> 00:24:45,400
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

392
00:24:45,483 --> 00:24:47,235
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
